Good question. Yes — with `#[derive(Default)]`, test code can use struct update syntax to specify only the fields that matter:

```rust
// Before: must spell out every field
let entry = TranscriptEntry {
    entry_type: Some("user".to_string()),
    sub_type: None,
    uuid: None,
    session_id: Some("s1".to_string()),
    timestamp: None,
    agent_id: None,
    is_sidechain: None,
    message: None,
    pr_number: None,
    pr_url: None,
    pr_repository: None,
};

// After: only fields you care about
let entry = TranscriptEntry {
    entry_type: Some("user".to_string()),
    session_id: Some("s1".to_string()),
    ..Default::default()
};
```

That said, this raises a broader question — there may be more types that could benefit. Let me audit the remaining value-object types for Default derivability.

